criteria.driver_alignment:
Represent — organized valuation around three methods and automation, showing intent to synthesize results;  
Implement — method-specific slides present numerical outcomes (DCF, comps, precedents);  
Validate — synthesis and sensitivity analysis demonstrate cross-method consistency.

Discover: framed the specific buyer-centric question (what KKR can pay) supporting a clear starting point;  
Implement: provided operating assumptions and noted Python automation for live testing of inputs/outputs;  
Reflect/Validate: reported summarized outputs (DCF ranges, comps, precedent) and sensitivity analysis to support conclusions.
